def has_switch(obj:item):
    # Determine whether the object has a switch
    symbol switch_exists=exists switch:item: has_switch(obj)
    return switch_exists

behavior preheat_heating_device(obj:item):
    body:
        if has_switch(obj):
            bind switch: item where:
                has_switch(obj)
            achieve is_on(obj)

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        # Preheat a skillet or oven
        # Attempt to preheat both the oven and the stove (skillet)
        foreach obj: item:
            if is_oven(obj) or is_stove(obj):
                preheat_heating_device(obj)

def is_bacon(item:item):
    # Determine if the item is bacon
    symbol is_bacon= is_food_bacon(item)
    return is_bacon

behavior cook_bacon_until_desired_crispiness(bacon:item, fryingpan:item):
    body:
        achieve on(bacon, fryingpan)
        # Ensure the bacon is on the frying pan
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove) and close_char(char, stove)
        achieve is_on(stove)
        # Ensure the stove is on
        observe(bacon, "Observe the crispiness of the bacon")
        # Check the crispiness using the observe behavior

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind fryingpan: item where:
            is_fryingpan(fryingpan)
        # Select a frying pan to cook the bacon
        
        foreach bacon: item:
            if is_bacon(bacon) and not closed(bacon):
                cook_bacon_until_desired_crispiness(bacon, fryingpan)

behavior cook_bacon(fryingpan:item, bacon:item, stove:item):
    body:
        achieve on(bacon, fryingpan) # Place the bacon on the frying pan
        achieve is_on(stove) # The stove should be turned on
        observe(fryingpan, "Observe until the bacon has reached the desired crispiness") # Continuou
sly monitor the bacons crispiness

        # Select an active stove
